Sherry Lynn https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sherry_Lynn 0 Sherry Lynn (born May 20, 1952) is an American voice actress, known for her young girl roles in anime, animated television series and video games. Her most notable role has been Sasami Jurai in the Tenchi Muyo! franchise.She is not to be confused with another Sherry Lynn, who appeared in The Shepherd in the Hills in 1964. In January 2010, in terms of total film gross, she was the Highest Grossing Female in the Movies and 23rd overall, with a total movie gross of over $2.5 billion US for her work in only 26 movies. She is also one of the co-founders and co-artistic directors of the Children's Theatre Group of Southern California.
